<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17565&amp;p=221808#p221808"><![CDATA[
Wisdom Tree's GB mapper is the one that's like BNROM, correct?<br /><br />Would a 2-chip mapper (74HC161 quad latch with binary counter + 74HC08 quad AND) implementing the same logic as <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_180" class="postlink">UNROM (180)</a> blow the power budget? (The '161 might need to be replaced with something different for clock and enable polarity.) At least it'd be mostly compatible with software designed for a standard MBC and no RAM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Jul 23, 2018 11:07 am</p><hr />
